%20both%20women%20in%20the%20labor%20force%2C%20and%20about%20gender%20and%20the%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20are%20two%20sets%20of%20issues%20that%20we%20know%20are%20important%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20get%20talked%20about%20enough%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20Goldin's%20most%20pivotal%20research%20looks%20at%20one%20of%20the%20big%20disconnects%20in%20the%20economy%3A%20Why%20earnings%20gaps%20still%20exist%20in%20high-income%20countries%2C%20even%20as%20women%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-says-women-are-becoming-better-educated-than-men-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreasingly%20better%20educated%20than%20men%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20working%20commensurate%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%2C%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20is%20what's%20called%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmotherhood-penalty%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emotherhood%20penalty%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Goldin%2C%20alongside%20Lawrence%20Katz%20and%20Marianne%20Bertrand%2C%20found%20that%20wage%20gaps%20are%20small%20at%20the%20onset%20of%20careers%20for%20men%20and%20women%20in%20similar%20fields%20and%20with%20similar%20experience.%20Indeed%2C%20in%20some%20metro%20areas%2C%20Gen%20Z%20and%20millennial%20women%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennial-women-earn-more-than-men-16-cities-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eout-earning%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20their%20male%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20that%20narrative%20flips%2C%20and%20Goldin's%20research%20determines%20why.%20A%2016-year-long%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholar.harvard.edu%2Ffiles%2Fgoldin%2Ffiles%2Fdynamics_of_the_gender_gap_for_young_professionals_in_the_financial_and_corporate_sectors.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20graduates%20from%20a%20top%20MBA%20school%20finds%20that%20female%20MBA%20graduates%20who%20have%20children%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20less%20job%20experience%2C%20more%20interruptions%20to%20their%20careers%2C%20and%20earnings%20decline%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that's%20not%20the%20case%20for%20their%20male%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20Nobel%20committee%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnobelprize.org%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2Fpopular-economicsciencesprize2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eexplains%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3Bas%20soon%20as%20the%20first%20child%20arrives%2C%20the%20trend%20changes%3B%20earnings%20immediately%20fall%20and%20do%20not%20increase%20at%20the%20same%20rate%20for%20women%20who%20have%20a%20child%20as%20they%20do%20for%20men%2C%20even%20if%20they%20have%20the%20same%20education%20and%20profession.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20essence%2C%20when%20women%20have%20children%2C%20their%20hours%20and%20earnings%20drop.%20That's%20the%20motherhood%20penalty.%20When%20men%20have%20kids%2C%20though%2C%20they're%20more%20likely%20to%20work%20even%20more%20hours%20and%20make%20more%20money%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20they%20benefit%20from%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhaving-a-child-increases-your-pay-but-only-if-youre-a-man%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efatherhood%20wage%20premium%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2023%2F03%2F01%2Fthe-enduring-grip-of-the-gender-pay-gap%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPew%20Research%20finds%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%202022%2C%20women%20ages%2025%20to%2034%20earned%2092%25%20of%20what%20men%20the%20same%20ages%20made%2C%20per%20Pew.%20But%20women%20ages%2035%20to%2044%2C%20who%20are%20in%20the%20peak%20age%20group%20for%20parenthood%2C%20made%20just%2083%25%20of%20what%20men%20the%20same%20ages%20took%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20gap%20that%20can%20follow%20women%20throughout%20their%20careers%20even%20when%20their%20kids%20get%20older%2C%20Goldin%20and%20economists%20Sari%20Pekkala%20Kerr%20and%20Claudia%20Olivetti%20found.%20Women%20do%20make%20up%20some%20ground%20once%20their%20kids%20are%20out%20of%20high%20school%3B%20they%20clock%20in%20for%20more%20hours%2C%20and%20their%20%26quot%3Bmotherhood%20penalty%26quot%3B%20is%20chipped%20away%20at.%20But%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20they're%20commensurate%20with%20their%20male%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20the%20time%20that%20women%20reach%20their%20mid%20fifties%20%E2%80%94%20I'm%20thinking%20especially%20about%20the%20college-educated%20women%20%E2%80%94%20the%20gains%20that%20men%20and%20fathers%20in%20particular%20have%20made%20in%20the%20labor%20market%20are%20so%20large%20that%20no%20matter%20what%20you%20do%20at%20that%20point%2C%20you%20can't%20make%20that%20ground%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Kerr%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20Wellesley%20College%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw30323%2Fw30323.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eco-authored%20that%20paper%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Goldin%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Bparental%20gender%20gap%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20Insider.%20Mothers%20can%20make%20up%20ground%20relative%20to%20non-mothers%2C%20Kerr%20said%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bthe%20gender%20gap%20is%20just%20way%20too%20large%20between%20parents.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20economics%2C%20having%20Goldin%20recognized%20like%20this%20means%20validation%20of%20the%20field%20that%20she's%20helped%20foster%20and%20mentor%2C%20Kerr%20said%2C%20and%20the%20hundreds%20of%20researchers%20who%20are%20chipping%20away%20at%20these%20topics.%20It%20also%20means%20that%20the%20question%20of%20the%20pay%20gap%20is%20now%20%26quot%3Bofficially%20recognized%20as%20a%20big%20key%20question%26quot%3B%20in%20economics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20lots%20of%20people%20doing%20such%20research%20now%2C%20and%20I%20think%20that%20this%20means%20that%20they'll%20see%20that%20it%20is%20important%20and%20that%20it's%20recognized%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-pay-gap-motherhood-fatherhood-nobel-prize-harvard-economist-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696878556000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652444a06561dd877e74fa19%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-pay-gap-motherhood-fatherhood-nobel-prize-harvard-economist-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Claudia%20Goldin%20has%20studied%20wage%20gaps%20and%20women's%20labor%20for%20decades.%20Now%20she's%20won%20the%20Nobel.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-pay-gap-motherhood-fatherhood-nobel-prize-harvard-economist-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BReminds%20Of%201973%26quot%3B%3A%20Israel-Gaza%20War%20Turns%20Jerusalem%20Into%20%26quot%3BGhost%20Town%26quot%3B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20usually%20bustling%20streets%20of%20Jerusalem%20were%20eerily%20quiet%20on%20Monday%20as%20deadly%20fighting%20between%20Israel%20and%20Palestinian%20militants%20raged%20for%20a%20third%20day%20in%20and%20around%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJerusalem%20is%20indeed%20a%20ghost%20town%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20May%20Bahbah%2C%20a%20Palestinian%20resident%20of%20Jerusalem%20in%20her%2040s.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20in%20fear%20and%20worried%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20AFP%2C%20standing%20next%20to%20a%20shuttered%20greengrocer.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPalestinians%20living%20in%20the%20city's%20Israeli-annexed%20east%20%26quot%3Bhave%20to%20go%20to%20their%20jobs%20but%20they%20are%20worried%20they%20might%20be%20abused%26quot%3B%20by%20Israeli%20forces%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20of%20the%20war%20situation%26quot%3B%2C%20said%20Bahbah.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENear%20Khan%20al-Zait%2C%20the%20Old%20City's%20main%20market%2C%20few%20shops%20had%20opened%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHazem%2C%2042%2C%20who%20did%20not%20wish%20to%20disclose%20his%20full%20name%2C%20came%20from%20the%20Palestinian%20neighbourhood%20of%20Silwan%20to%20run%20some%20errands%20and%20was%20visibly%20angry.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20(Israeli)%20police%20officers%20asked%20me%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20car%2C%20and%20they%20searched%20it%20and%20found%20an%20electrical%20outlet%20tester%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20them%20slapped%20me%20so%20hard%2C%20and%20when%20they%20wanted%20to%20attack%20me%2C%20an%20Arab%20officer%20stopped%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20city's%20west%2C%20Israeli%20pensioner%20Sara%2C%2070%2C%20was%20sitting%20on%20a%20bench%20after%20her%20morning%20walk%20along%20the%20city's%20normally%20busy%20main%20roads%20that%20were%20now%20almost%20deserted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20did%20not%20see%20many%20people%20in%20the%20streets%2C%20but%20it's%20natural%2C%20it's%20war!%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20all%20worried...%20those%20who%20have%20someone%20in%20the%20army%20are%20very%20anxious.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20atmosphere%20around%20the%20city%20%26quot%3Breminds%20me%20of%201973%26quot%3B%2C%20when%20Arab%20armies%20attacked%20Israel%20in%20a%20war%20that%20scarred%20the%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20First%20Station%20commercial%20centre%2C%20which%20was%20full%20of%20people%20just%20days%20ago%20during%20the%20Jewish%20holiday%20of%20Sukkot%2C%20businesses%20had%20ground%20to%20a%20halt%2C%20with%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20storefronts%20showing%20%26quot%3Bclosed%26quot%3B%20signs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20school%20week%20has%20not%20started%20in%20either%20the%20city's%20east%20or%20west%20since%20violence%20broke%20out%20early%20Saturday%20with%20a%20surprise%20attack%20by%20Hamas%20militants%20targeting%20southern%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20some%20700%20people%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20Israel%20and%20560%20in%20the%20blockaded%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20according%20to%20official%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E'Dying%20from%20the%20inside'%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EStrong%20winds%20and%20rain%20on%20Monday%20have%20further%20dissuaded%20Jerusalemites%20from%20leaving%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20feel%20like%20we%20are%20dying%20from%20the%20inside%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Itamar%20Taragan%2C%20manager%20of%20the%20First%20Station%20compound%2C%20which%20he%20said%20would%20reopen%20%26quot%3Bnot%20tomorrow%20and%20not%20after%20tomorrow%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20%26quot%3Bopen%20their%20restaurants%20only%20to%20cook%20for%20soldiers%2C%20firefighters%2C%20things%20like%20this%26quot%3B%2C%20he%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20breathe%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Taragan.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20watching%20TV%20all%20day%2C%20looking%20at...%20videos%20of%20the%20people%20who%20were%20abducted%2C%20and%20even%20if%20it's%20not%20your%20children%2C%20you're%20in%20shock.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPamela%20Auerbach%20and%20Jane%20Medved%20stepped%20out%20of%20one%20of%20the%20few%20open%20shops%2C%20an%20organic%20supermarket%2C%20onto%20a%20%26quot%3Bquiet%26quot%3B%20city%2C%20said%20Auerbach%2C%2056%2C%20a%20lawyer%20who%20splits%20her%20time%20between%20Israel%20and%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20saw%20many%20young%20people%20offering%20help%20to%20families%20distressed%20by%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20Medved%2C%20a%2067-year-old%20university%20professor%2C%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20are%20busy%2C%20that's%20all.%20Busy%20working%20from%20home.%20Busy%20organising%20the%20he