20deal%20with%20%E2%80%94%20relatives.%20Right%20from%20telling%20my%20father%20he%20was%20wasting%20money%20on%20my%20education%20to%20advising%20him%20to%20marry%20me%20off%2C%20they%20tried%20their%20best%20to%20discourage%20him.%20They%20even%20tried%20forcing%20me%20to%20cook%20and%20be%20like%20the%20other%20girls%20they%20knew%2C%20but%20my%20dad%20became%20my%20shield%20against%20these%20taunts%20and%20pressure.%20And%20that%E2%80%99s%20how%20I%20grew%20up%20protected%20from%20the%20outside%20world.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20in%20later%20years%20I%20began%20to%20appreciate%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F331721%2Frajasthan-government-school-teacher-trains-self-defense-to-girls-with-disabilities-national-award%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethis%20side%20of%20life%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20always.%20In%20school%2C%20I%20remember%20writing%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EBauji%3C%2Fem%3E%20(father)%20is%20a%20businessman%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3EAmma%20%3C%2Fem%3E(mother)%20is%20a%20tailor.%E2%80%9D%20I%20was%20scared%20I%20would%20get%20bullied%20if%20my%20friends%20discovered%20my%20father%20ran%20a%20%3Cem%3Epaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Ethela%20%3C%2Fem%3E(betel%20leaf%20stall).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20even%20remember%20asking%20him%20repeatedly%20why%20he%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20like%20the%20other%20parents%2C%20who%20worked%20in%20offices%20and%20wore%20ironed%20shirts.%20His%20response%20would%20always%20be%20the%20same%2C%20%E2%80%9CMoney%20isn%E2%80%99t%20everything%20in%20life.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20did%20not%20understand%20the%20value%20of%20his%20words%2C%20but%20now%20I%20do.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20was%20a%20time%20I%20thought%20I%20did%20not%20have%20as%20much%20as%20other%20children%2C%20today%20I%20realise%20I%20always%20had%20something%20that%20none%20of%20the%20others%20did%20%E2%80%94%20a%20father%20who%20believe