he%20DPR%20within%20three%20months%20when%20Dahal%20visited%20New%20Delhi%20from%20late%20May%20to%20early%20June%20this%20year%2C%20officials%20of%20the%20two%20countries%20accelerated%20their%20talks%20at%20different%20levels%20on%20the%20Pancheshwar%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20sticking%20point%20of%20bilateral%20negotiation%20has%20been%20which%20country%20gets%20how%20much%20benefit%20from%20the%20multipurpose%20project%2C%20which%20aims%20at%20not%20only%20producing%20electricity%20but%20also%20irrigating%20vast%20swathes%20of%20India%20and%20some%20areas%20of%20Nepal%2C%20besides%20controlling%20floods.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COnce%20again%2C%20we%20could%20not%20reach%20a%20conclusion%20on%20determining%20the%20benefits%20to%20each%20side%20from%20the%20project%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Nabin%20Raj%20Singh%2C%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Energy%2C%20Water%20Resources%20and%20Irrigation.%20%E2%80%9COur%20point%20was%20that%20we%20get%20negligible%20benefits%20from%20this%20project%20in%20areas%20of%20irrigation%20and%20flood%20control%20while%20the%20Indian%20side%20wants%20to%20keep%20the%20benefits%20for%20itself.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Singh%2C%20there%20will%20be%20equal%20benefits%20for%20both%20sides%20in%20power%20availability.%20Quantifying%20the%20benefit%20for%20each%20side%20is%20important%20because%20investments%20will%20be%20based%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20Mahakali%20Treaty%20signed%20in%201996%2C%20the%20two%20sides%20have%20agreed%20in%20principle%20that%20the%20cost%20would%20be%20shared%20based%20on%20the%20benefits%20to%20each%20side%20in%20the%20areas%20of%20power%2C%20irrigation%20and%20flood%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESingh%20also%20said%20the%20two%20sides%20have%20agreed%20to%20hold%20another%20meeting%20of%20experts%20soon%20to%20reach%20consensus%20on%20the%20DPR.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDifferences%20over%20the%20draft%20DPR%20have%20put%20the%206%2C480-megawatt%20project%20in%20limbo%20for%20nearly%20three%20decades%20since%20the%20Mahakali%20Treaty%E2%80%99s%20signing%20in%201996.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20treaty%2C%20the%20two%20countries%20had%20prepared%20a%20separate%20DPR.%20India%E2%80%99s%20state-owned%20Water%20and%20Power%20Consultancy%20Services%20(WAPCOS)%20Ltd%20prepared%20and%20submitted%20the%20DPR%20in%202016%20by%20merging%20the%20two%20reports.%20Still%2C%20the%20two%20sides%20were%20not%20on%20the%20same%20page%20on%20several%20issues%20of%20the%20joint%20DPR%2C%20consequently%20delaying%20the%20final%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20fourth%20meeting%20of%20experts%20in%20late%20July%20had%20instructed%20the%20WAPCOS%20Ltd%20to%20revise%20the%20DPR%20in%20line%20with%20the%20understanding%20reached%20earlier.%20WAPCOS%20recently%20submitted%20a%20draft%20DPR%20to%20both%20sides.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20shared%20each%20others%E2%80%99%20views%20on%20the%20draft%20and%20reached%20an%20understanding%20on%20a%20lot%20of%20other%20issues%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Singh.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20the%20cost-benefit%20issue%20could%20not%20be%20resolved%20at%20this%20meeting.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPrithvi%20Man%20Shrestha%20is%20a%20political%20reporter%20for%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Kathmandu%20Post%3Cem%3E%2C%20covering%20the%20governance-related%20issues%20including%20corruption%20and%20irregularities%20in%20the%20government%20machinery.%20Before%20joining%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Kathmandu%20Post%3Cem%3E%20in%202009%2C%20he%20worked%20at%20nepalnews.com%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3ERising%20Nepal%3Cem%3E%20primarily%20covering%20the%20issues%20of%20political%20and%20economic%20affairs%20for%20three%20years.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkathmandupost.com%2Fmoney%2F2023%2F10%2F09%2Fnepal-india-fail-to-finalise-pancheshwar-detailed-project-report%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20Kathmandu%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22publi